# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Atlas — environment (CLIENT-SAFE values ONLY)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Copy to apps/mobile/.env.local and fill in. The mobile app reads EXPO_PUBLIC_*
#  values at bundle time. These are PUBLIC by design: the Supabase anon key is
#  RLS-gated, so it is safe to ship in the native bundle (CLAUDE.md §11.3).

EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=YOUR_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  DO NOT PUT SECRETS HERE  (CLAUDE.md §11.3 / §11.4)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  The service_role key and any LLM provider key must NEVER appear in an
#  EXPO_PUBLIC_* variable or in the RN bundle. They live ONLY in the Supabase
#  Edge Function environment, set via `supabase secrets set ...`:
#
#    SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY   → edge function env only
#    LLM_PROVIDER_API_KEY        → edge function env only (Decision D4, Law-25 provider)
#
#  The native client uses the anon key only.
